operations.examples:
Limit the amount of documents using <em>limit</em> <br><br><pre><code class="json" >unix> curl -X PUT --data @- --dump - http://localhost:8529/_api/simple/all
{ "collection": "products", "skip": 2, "limit" : 2 }

HTTP/1.1 201 Created
content-type: application/json; charset=utf-8

{ 
  "result" : [ 
    { 
      "_id" : "products/175622076", 
      "_rev" : "175622076", 
      "_key" : "175622076", 
      "Hello2" : "World2" 
    }, 
    { 
      "_id" : "products/175228860", 
      "_rev" : "175228860", 
      "_key" : "175228860", 
      "Hello1" : "World1" 
    } 
  ], 
  "hasMore" : false, 
  "count" : 2, 
  "error" : false, 
  "code" : 201 
}

</code></pre><br>Using a <em>batchSize</em> value <br><br><pre><code class="json" >unix> curl -X PUT --data @- --dump - http://localhost:8529/_api/simple/all
{ "collection": "products", "batchSize" : 3 }

HTTP/1.1 201 Created
content-type: application/json; charset=utf-8

{ 
  "result" : [ 
    { 
      "_id" : "products/178112444", 
      "_rev" : "178112444", 
      "_key" : "178112444", 
      "Hello2" : "World2" 
    }, 
    { 
      "_id" : "products/178767804", 
      "_rev" : "178767804", 
      "_key" : "178767804", 
      "Hello4" : "World4" 
    }, 
    { 
      "_id" : "products/179095484", 
      "_rev" : "179095484", 
      "_key" : "179095484", 
      "Hello5" : "World5" 
    } 
  ], 
  "hasMore" : true, 
  "id" : "179292092", 
  "count" : 5, 
  "error" : false, 
  "code" : 201 
}

</code></pre><br>

